title: Does self-talk {conjure, defend, obscure} the self?
pid: cf075eee-56aa-4861-a280-6b8fe648f4ce
body: |2-
  Maybe the words in my head tie me to my sense of myself.
  They certainly tie me to *a* sense of myself.
  The self that remains when I quiet those words,
    might be one I know less well, and
    might be a {more general, bigger, more empathetic} one.
